  <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/images/logo.png">
</head>
<body>
  <header>

    <div class="logo">
      <img src="/images/logo.png" height="60px" alt="Logo">
    </div>
    <div class="nav">
      <div class="game-btn">
        <p>Games</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/leaderboards">
        <div>
          <p>Leaderboards</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <div class="inspiration-btn">
        <p>Inspiration</p>
      </div>
      <!-- <a href="/leaderboards">
        <div>
          <p>Leaderboard</p>
        </div>
      </a> -->
    </div>
    <% if(locals.username){ %>
  <div class="dropdown login" style="margin-right: 10px;">
    <button class="btn btn-secondary dropdown-toggle" type="button" data-bs-toggle="dropdown" style="color:black; background-color:#F4F8D3; font-size:25px;">
      <%= username %>
    </button>

    <ul class="dropdown-menu">
      <li>
        <button class="dropdown-item" id="logoutBtn" style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', 'Lucida Sans', Arial, sans-serif;">Logout</button>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <form id="logoutForm" action="/logout" method="POST" style="display:none;"></form>

  <script>
    document.getElementById('logoutBtn').addEventListener('click', function() {
      document.getElementById('logoutForm').submit();
    });
  </script>

    <% }  else {%>  
    <div class="login">
      <a href="/login">
      <div>
        <p>Login/Register</p>
      </div>
    </a>
    </div>
    <% } %>
    
  </header>

  <section class="banner">
    <div class="title">
      <h1 class="anton-regular">Airball</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="subtitle">
      <h2 class="anton-sc-regular">The Go-To NBA Quiz App for Elite Ball Knowers</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="description">
      <p>
      Put your ball knowledge to the test with built-in trivia covering the most niche corners of the NBA universe.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="gif">
    <img src="/images/dame-gif.gif" height="400px" width="400px">
  </div>
  
  <section class="games">
    <h3 class="anton-sc-regular">Game List: </h3>
    <a href="/startCollegeCheck">
      <div class="college-check">
        <p>Play CollegeCheck</p>
      </div>
    </a>
    
    <a href="/startJerseyCheck">
      <div class="jersey-check">
      <p>Play NumberCheck</p>
    </div>
    </a>

    <div class="coming-soon">
      <p>More Games are Coming Soon........</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="inspiration">
    <div>
      <h3 class="anton-sc-regular">What Sparked this Project: </h3>
    </div>

    <div>
      <p>
      One of my favorite podcasts to catch up with hoops is Numbers on the Board, hosted by Kenny, 
      Mike, DMills, and Pierre. They cover everything from trades and signings to game-by-game 
      analysis, and every now and then they quiz each other to see who’s the most locked in. 
      My favorite is “CollegeCheck,” where Pierre names a random player and the others have 
      to guess what college they went to.
      </p>
      <p>
        As a self-proclaimed ballknower, mastering this niche trivia felt like bragging rights
        — so I started digging for APIs with player college data and eventually found one.
      </p>
      <p>
        But I didn’t want to stop there. What if I built a collection of quizzes that tested every 
        corner of the league — the kind of deep-cut knowledge only true hoop heads would know?
      </p>
      <p>
        That’s the vision behind Airball: a site where elite ball knowers can put their basketball
        knowledge to the test.
      </p>
    </div>
    
  </section>

